President Obama called Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi of Iraq to congratulate him on the approval of a new Iraqi government. The President praised the efforts of Prime Minister Abadi and other Iraqi leaders in forming a new, inclusive government. They discussed the need for the United States and Iraq to continue working with the international community to counter the threat posed by ISIL. Prime Minister Abadi expressed his commitment to working with all communities in Iraq and regional and international partners to strengthen Iraq's capabilities against this common enemy. Both leaders emphasized the importance of the new government taking concrete steps to address the aspirations and legitimate grievances of the Iraqi people. They also expressed their support for a strong strategic partnership between the United States and Iraq and the President emphasized his commitment to coordinating closely with Prime Minister Abadi and his government to combat ISIL.